definition.value: A keto-D-gluconate that is the conjugate base of 2-dehydro-D-gluconic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group.
A monosaccharide sulfate consisting of D-glucose having the sulfate group at the 6-position.
An oxo dicarboxylate obtained by deprotonation of both carboxy groups of 2-oxoglutaric acid.
A sulfur-containing amino acid that is butyric acid bearing an amino substituent at position 2 and a methylthio substituent at position 4.
